.TH "HISTCLEAN" "1" "2026-06-22" "" "General Commands Manual"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
histclean - clean shell history file
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBhistclean\fR [options]
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Clean duplicate shell commands from history files in-place, while
preserving the most recent unique occurrence of each command.\&
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
.RS 4
Show help message and exit.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-d\fR, \fB--dry-run\fR
.RS 4
Print the resulted output to stdout without modifying anything.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-b\fR, \fB--backup\fR
.RS 4
Create a .\&backup copy of the history file before modifying it.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-i\fR, \fB--input\fR <FILE>
.RS 4
Read history from <file> instead of the default shell
history file.\&
\fBhistclean\fR will try first to lookup history file
using $HISTFILE, then using $HOME/.\&bash_history.\& If no \fBhistory\fR file was
founded, a \fBHistoryFileNotFound\fR error will raise.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-o\fR, \fB--output\fR <FILE>
.RS 4
Write resulted output to the specified <file> instead of overwriting
the input file.\&
Running the command multiple times to the same \fBoutput\fR will overwrite
it.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.PP
\fBHISTFILE\fR
.RS 4
Path to the shell history file.\& If not set, defaults to
\fB$HOME\fR/.\&bash_history.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBHOME\fR
.RS 4
Used to construct the default history path when \fBHISTFILE\fR is not
set.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH LIMITATIONS
.RS 4
Currently, \fBhistclean\fR only have implementation of \fB.\&bash_histor\fR file
with their timestamps.\&
.br
\fBhistclean\fR well work correctly with \fBEXTENDED_HISTORY\fR turned off.\&
Meaning it dose not have an implementaion for parsing \fB.\&zsh_history\fR
file with their timestamps.\&
.RE
